<br>
In response to the jewelcraft question...if anyone is still trying to make a go of jewelcraft from the ground up in this economy they have my deepest respect.  You aren't seeing jewelers pricing the stuff almost at all anymore, you are seeing people selling their old jewelry again, often people who have no clue.  You can get great prices, or you can see the insane.  You want a good clue of how little most people know about jewelcraft and jewelry?  Browse a list of the gems for sale.  I mean the Store Bought gems.  Some guy wants 50 platinum for his carnelian.  I've also bought a sapphire for as much, and I can SELL it for 95 straight back to a vendor.  Yesterday I bought 100 peridots for 8.5 platinum each.  I'll use them eventually, but even if I don't I can sell them for slightly more than 9.5 each.  When it comes to gems and jewelry, people have no friggin clue at all.  Is it any wonder all the sane jewelers have retired?  I occassionally do diamond and blue diamond stuff, or gem-studded chains, or work with Royal Velium armor.  Nothing else at all.  There's just no point.<br>
